# ============================================================
# env-space — Environment Variable Documentation
# Agentic Mechanical Engineer
# ============================================================
#
# This file documents EVERY environment variable the project may use.
# It is documentation only — actual values go in `.env` (copied from
# `.env.example`).
#
# !! SECURITY WARNING !!
# Never commit real secrets to this repository. `.env` is gitignored.
# Never paste keys into code, tests, docs, or commit messages.
# The SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY and any *_SECRET values are SERVER-ONLY
# and must never reach a browser/frontend bundle.
#
# The deterministic MVP demo (`make demo`) requires NO environment
# variables at all. Everything below is optional until the feature that
# uses it is enabled.
#
# Format per variable:
#   NAME | required? | what it does | when needed | how to get it | example
# ------------------------------------------------------------

# ---------------- Core runtime ----------------

MODEL_PROVIDER
  Required: optional (default: "deterministic")
  What: Selects the reasoning backend for the AI agent layer. One of:
        deterministic | anthropic | openai | openrouter | ollama | vllm | local
  When: Only when you switch from the deterministic MVP pipeline to
        LLM-backed agents (Sprint 8+). "deterministic" runs fully offline.
  How to get: n/a — pick a value.
  Example: MODEL_PROVIDER=anthropic

MODEL_NAME
  Required: optional
  What: The specific model used by the selected provider
        (e.g. claude-fable-5 for Anthropic, or a local vLLM-served model id).
  When: Only when MODEL_PROVIDER is not "deterministic".
  Example: MODEL_NAME=claude-fable-5

STORAGE_DIR
  Required: optional (default: "./outputs")
  What: Directory where all generated artifacts (JSON, STL, CSV, reports)
        are written. Local filesystem is the MVP storage backend.
  When: Always used; only set it if you want a non-default location.
  Example: STORAGE_DIR=./outputs

MAX_CAD_COMPLEXITY
  Required: optional (default: 100000)
  What: Guardrail — upper bound on CAD job complexity (approximate
        facet/feature budget) so a bad parameter set cannot generate a
        multi-gigabyte mesh or hang the CAD kernel.
  When: Always enforced by the CAD service.
  Example: MAX_CAD_COMPLEXITY=100000

CAD_MAX_ITERATIONS
  Required: optional (default: 5)
  What: Iteration budget for the generative-CAD optimization loop (model
        writes CAD -> build -> engineering checks -> revise). Each
        iteration is one LLM call plus a sandboxed CAD build, so this is
        the primary COST control on metered API credits / GPU time.
  When: Generative mode only (arbitrary-object prompts with an LLM
        provider configured).
  How to get: n/a — pick a number; 3-5 sensible, higher burns more credits.
  Example: CAD_MAX_ITERATIONS=5

ALLOW_EXTERNAL_PART_SEARCH
  Required: optional (default: false)
  What: Boolean gate. External supplier/part APIs (Nexar/Octopart etc.)
        are never called unless this is explicitly "true". Keeps the MVP
        fully offline and prevents surprise API usage/costs.
  When: Enable only when BOM enrichment via supplier APIs is implemented.
  Example: ALLOW_EXTERNAL_PART_SEARCH=false

# ---------------- LLM providers (AI agent layer) ----------------

ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
  Required: optional (required only if MODEL_PROVIDER=anthropic)
  What: API key for Anthropic Claude/Fable models — the primary
        reasoning model target for this project.
  When: LLM-based requirements extraction / architecture proposals.
  How to get: Anthropic Console -> API Keys.
  Link: https://console.anthropic.com/
  Example: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-key-here

OPENAI_API_KEY
  Required: optional (required only if MODEL_PROVIDER=openai)
  What: API key for OpenAI models as an alternative provider.
  When: Same as above, with OpenAI backend.
  How to get: OpenAI platform -> API keys.
  Link: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
  Example: OPENAI_API_KEY=your-openai-key-here

OPENROUTER_API_KEY
  Required: optional (required only if MODEL_PROVIDER=openrouter)
  What: API key for OpenRouter — single API that routes to many models
        (useful for open-weights models without self-hosting).
  How to get: OpenRouter dashboard -> Keys.
  Link: https://openrouter.ai/keys
  Example: OPENROUTER_API_KEY=your-openrouter-key-here

FIREWORKS_API_KEY
  Required: optional (required only if MODEL_PROVIDER=fireworks)
  What: API key for Fireworks AI serverless inference (hackathon sponsor
        platform; $50 credits for participants, +$50 for AMD AI Developer
        Program members).
  How to get: fireworks.ai -> sign in -> account settings -> API keys.
  Link: https://fireworks.ai
  Note (verified 2026-07-03): serverless catalogs vary per account — list
        yours via GET /inference/v1/models; Gemma may not be serverless.
  Example: FIREWORKS_API_KEY=your-fireworks-key-here

VLLM_BASE_URL
  Required: optional (default: http://localhost:8001/v1)
  What: Base URL of a self-hosted OpenAI-compatible inference server, used
        when MODEL_PROVIDER=vllm or local. For the hackathon this points at
        a vLLM server running Gemma on an AMD Developer Cloud Instinct
        instance (ROCm).
  When: MODEL_PROVIDER=vllm | local.
  How to get: PREREQUISITE — AMD AI Developer Program membership
        (https://www.amd.com/en/developer.html, manual approval 2-3 days),
        then provision an instance at https://devcloud.amd.com/ and run
        `vllm serve google/gemma-3-27b-it` (needs HF_TOKEN with the Gemma
        license accepted). The AMD devcloud API token itself is a
        deployment credential, not read by this app.
  Example: VLLM_BASE_URL=http://203.0.113.7:8000/v1

# Note: MODEL_PROVIDER=ollama / vllm / local use a base URL convention
# (OPENAI-compatible endpoints); no key is needed for a local server.
# If your local server needs a key, reuse OPENAI_API_KEY with the
# provider set accordingly.

# ---------------- Persistence (optional) ----------------

DATABASE_URL
  Required: optional
  What: Postgres connection string. Unlocks persistent design history
        instead of filesystem-only storage.
  When: Only when the Postgres storage backend is enabled (post-MVP).
  How to get: Your Postgres host, or Supabase project settings ->
        Database -> Connection string.
  Example: DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/mea

SUPABASE_URL
  Required: optional
  What: Supabase project URL, if using Supabase for storage/auth.
  How to get: Supabase dashboard -> Project Settings -> API.
  Link: https://supabase.com/dashboard
  Example: SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co

SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
  Required: optional
  What: Supabase public (anon) key — safe for client-side use with RLS.
  How to get: Supabase dashboard -> Project Settings -> API.
  Example: SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY
  Required: optional
  What: Supabase service-role key. Bypasses row-level security.
  !! SERVER-ONLY. Never expose to the frontend or commit it. !!
  How to get: Supabase dashboard -> Project Settings -> API.
  Example: SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=server-only-never-expose

# ---------------- Automation / deployment (optional) ----------------

GITHUB_TOKEN
  Required: optional
  What: GitHub token for wiki automation in CI, repo operations,
        or GitHub Actions that push generated docs.
  When: Only for CI automation; local `make wiki` needs no token.
  How to get: GitHub -> Settings -> Developer settings -> Tokens.
  Link: https://github.com/settings/tokens
  Example: GITHUB_TOKEN=your-github-token-here

VERCEL_TOKEN
  Required: optional
  What: Deploy token for the (future) Next.js frontend.
  When: Frontend deployment only (Sprint 7+).
  Link: https://vercel.com/account/tokens
  Example: VERCEL_TOKEN=your-vercel-token-here

VERCEL_ORG_ID / VERCEL_PROJECT_ID
  Required: optional
  What: Identify the Vercel org/project for CI deployments.
  How to get: `vercel link` writes them to .vercel/project.json.
  Example: VERCEL_ORG_ID=team_xxxx / VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=prj_xxxx

RENDER_API_KEY
  Required: optional
  What: Backend deployment on Render.
  Link: https://dashboard.render.com/account/api-keys
  Example: RENDER_API_KEY=your-render-key-here

RAILWAY_TOKEN
  Required: optional
  What: Backend deployment on Railway (alternative to Render).
  Link: https://railway.com/account/tokens
  Example: RAILWAY_TOKEN=your-railway-token-here

# ---------------- ML / observability (optional) ----------------

HF_TOKEN
  Required: optional
  What: Hugging Face token for gated models/datasets (e.g. pulling
        open-weights models for local/vLLM inference).
  Link: https://huggingface.co/settings/tokens
  Example: HF_TOKEN=your-huggingface-token-here

WANDB_API_KEY
  Required: optional
  What: Weights & Biases experiment tracking (e.g. evaluating agent
        output quality across prompt/model versions).
  Link: https://wandb.ai/authorize
  Example: WANDB_API_KEY=your-wandb-key-here

SENTRY_DSN
  Required: optional
  What: Sentry error tracking DSN for the backend API in production.
  How to get: Sentry project settings -> Client Keys (DSN).
  Link: https://sentry.io/
  Example: SENTRY_DSN=https://examplePublicKey@o0.ingest.sentry.io/0

# ---------------- Sourcing / CAD cloud (optional, future) ----------------

NEXAR_CLIENT_ID / NEXAR_CLIENT_SECRET
  Required: optional
  What: Octopart/Nexar API credentials for real component sourcing and
        live pricing in the BOM (replaces curated placeholder prices).
  When: Only when ALLOW_EXTERNAL_PART_SEARCH=true and BOM enrichment
        is implemented.
  Link: https://nexar.com/api
  Example: NEXAR_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id / NEXAR_CLIENT_SECRET=server-only

ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY / ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY
  Required: optional
  What: Onshape cloud CAD API keys — future integration for pushing
        generated geometry into a full cloud CAD environment.
  Link: https://dev-portal.onshape.com/
  Example: ONSHAPE_ACCESS_KEY=your-access-key / ONSHAPE_SECRET_KEY=server-only

# ============================================================
# TL;DR: `make demo` needs nothing. Add keys only when you turn on
# the feature that uses them. Keep secrets out of git, always.
# ============================================================
